In a typical synthesis process of CDs, different ratios of dried banana stem and phosphoric acid (1:1, 1:2, 1:3) were soaked in certain amount of double distilled water for 10 h. The separate mixtures were then placed in a Teflon-lined stainless-steel autoclave and heated at 180 °C for 6 h. The autoclave was then cooled to room temperature. Subsequently, the product thus obtained was separated by centrifugation and the resultant supernatant was further purified by dialysis in a dialysis bag (1000 MWCO) for 24 h. A yellowish-brown color solution was obtained containing CDs. The obtained CDs were kept in a refrigerator at 10 °C for further use. The detailed scheme of CDs formation is displayed in Scheme 1
                        . The reaction conditions with the highest quantum yield have been studied by varying the temperature (140 °C and 160 °C) [Table 1
                        ].
